Apache-Syntax-Highlight-Universal 0.0.2
=======================================

This package is a mod_perl (1.0 and 2.0) module that provides syntax
highlighting for any code. This module is a wrapper around
Syntax::Highlight::Universal written by Wladimir Palant.

See perldoc Apache::Syntax::Highlight::Universal for module documentation and use

Note: This module was originally inspired by the Apache::Syntax::Highlight::Perl
module, written by Enrico Sorcinelli <enrico@sorcinelli.it>.

CHANGES FROM PREVIOUS VERSION

	- Fixed ticket #7 Makefile.PL/META.yml are missing SOME prereq
	- Fixed ticket #2 Do not make directories etc. a requirement
	- Fixed ticket #4 Output XHTML only if the user agent supports it
	- Fixed ticket #3 Add a class attribute to each pre tag
	- Fixed ticket #5 Remove charset meta tag
	
See 'Changes' file in this distribution for complete history revision

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

   o mod_perl 1 or 2 (of course)
   o Syntax::Highlight::Perl >= 1.00
   o File::MimeInfo >= 0.11

